    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>NNos <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/304">Atenulfus</persName> divina
                        ordinante providentia <rs key="#Princeps">Langobardorum gentis
                        princeps</rs>, <rs key="#Intercessory">per rogum</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/302" key="#Abbots">Baldoin</persName> venerabili <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbati</rs> karissimo patri nostro, concessimus in <rs
                            key="#Churches">aecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/216"
                            >sancti Benedicti</orgName>, que est <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cella</rs> in <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit">loco</rs> Caudi, hos
                        homines <rs key="#Freedman">libertis</rs>: <persName key="#Freedman"><name
                                ref="Leo">Leonem</name></persName>, <persName key="#Freedman"><name
                                ref="Bernardus">Bernardum</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Freedman"><name ref="Lupus">Lupum</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Freedman"><name ref="Carrarus">Carrarum</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Freedman"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannem</name></persName>, <persName key="#Freedman"><name
                                ref="Silvus">Silbum</name></persName>, Iohannem, <persName
                            key="#Freedman"><name ref="Stefanus">Stefanum</name></persName>,
                        commorantes <rs key="#Confinia">in pertinentia</rs> de predicta caella. In
                        ea videlicet ratione illos in predicta cella iam dictos homines concessimus,
                        ut nec comes, nec gastaldeus, nec iudex, nec ullus nostri principatus
                        subiciens illos tangere aut molestare in aliquo presumat, aut in angariam,
                        aut in hoste, aut in quocumque <rs key="#Operae">servitio publico</rs> illos
                        minare audeat, et nec censum, nec dationes, nec pensiones, nec ullum
                        servitium ab eis existere querat, sed ab omni exactione publica securi et
                        quieti maneant amodo et deinceps perpetuis temporibus, et quanti <rs
                            key="#Natio">homines extranei</rs> qui non sunt <rs key="#Fines">de
                            nostris finibus</rs> in pertinentia de predicta caella venerint ad
                        habitandum, similiter sub ista <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium"
                            >defensione</rs>. Ex iussione predicte potestati scripsi ego <persName
                            key="#Professional_writer #Clergy/religious_persons"><name ref="Ursus"
                                >Ursus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Clergy/religious_persons">clericus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Professional_writer">scriba</rs> in anno decimo principatus eius,
                        mense Ianuario, indictione prima. <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/196"
                            >Maielpotus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> XX(s) VI(s). Hic recepit a predicto principe
                            <rs key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">preceptum</rs> in hunc modum
                        continentem. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
